race.comment: Competitive. SOLAR ORBIT (11) is close to breaking through after finishing in the placings his last two, most recently when missing 1L over 2200m at Sapphire Coast. Has a 2kg claim today and the blinkers on for the first time. Can position forward and should get every chance. I DOUBT IT (14) has been narrowly beaten her last two over a mile in decent Maidens. Steps up to a middle distance for the first time and will race handy. Seasoned enough and should see it out. SWIFT GUN (6) has the ability and is likely looking for the middle distance. The gate is sticky but he is back in grade and on song would be right in it. SHARE OUR SECRET (10) led beaten a whisker this track/trip in a CL1 and then found the grade a bit rich at Canberra. Has to skip over from a wide barrier but a much better effort is on the cards.
